## 2. Reference Template Assessment (coleam00/remote-mcp-server-with-auth)

Reviewed. **Borrow the patterns, reject the platform.**

**Borrow:**
- Modular tools layout — one tool per file under `src/tools/`, centralized `registerAllTools()` registration
- Zod-style schema validation on every tool input
- Dual transport: Streamable HTTP at `/mcp` (primary) + stdio for local single-tenant use
- Role/permission-gated tool availability (their GitHub-username allowlist → our risk-tier + auth-context gating)
- Error sanitization before returning to the client; structured logging with user/tenant context on every call
- MCP Inspector as the standard manual test harness; comprehensive unit tests with mocked backends
- Optional Sentry (or OpenTelemetry) hook for production monitoring

**Reject (wrong for this project):**
- **Cloudflare Workers runtime** — cannot host a PowerShell runtime; the Teams admin surface requires `pwsh` + the MicrosoftTeams module. We need a container/VM-hostable process.
- **GitHub OAuth identity** — wrong identity plane. Client auth is bearer/mTLS for the local phase; tenant-side auth is Entra app-only with certificates.
- **`executeDatabase`-style generic "run anything" write tool** — the single most important thing NOT to copy. Our writes are enumerated, single-purpose, schema-validated tools only.
- Durable Objects / KV state — our state model is per-tenant PowerShell sessions in-process + append-only audit files.

